reviewText: The original Dells were as talented a quintet in the r&b field as any group ever was ... but they were 'ghetto' all the way as evidenced by the on stage profanities they engaged in for this performance.  The quality of this dvd is not as good as it could've and should be but I'm haunted by this veteran group's disrespect for their audience when the former engaged in this sort of lowlife profanities.  Some may think I am too sensitive in relating these facts but whether or not a performer is 'ghetto' or not, it is imperative that performers from the ghetto maintain a higher professionalism than their roots would mandate.  Bravo for the Dells talent, boos for their recorded performance herein.

reviewText: I'm sorry, I love the Dells, but I would not recommend this DVD to anyone.  Unfortunately, they have just gotten too old to be singing anymore.  They struggled to walk out on the stage, let alone sing. It hurt to watch them attempt to hit the notes.
